{
  format: 1
  name: liasse-json-byte-integrity-vs-canonical-identity-unspecified
  suite: scenario
  spec: ["§D.4", "§D.5", "§19.5", "§19.8"]
  tags: ["integrity", "tampering"]
  note: '''Attack: replace `liasse.json` inside an exported artifact with a DIFFERENT
but still structurally valid definition, and leave `manifest.definition.identity`
untouched. Does restore detect the substitution?

The spec leaves this unpinned:
- §19.5 gives the manifest a `definition: { identity, path }` member that is the
  §D.4 canonical SHA-256, but liasse.json is NOT listed among the byte-checksummed
  members (`state`, `history`, `included_modules`, and `entries`, where §19.5 says
  `entries` "covers every required direct archive entry other than manifest.json").
  Whether liasse.json also appears in `entries` (byte-checksummed) or is covered
  ONLY by `definition.identity` is not stated.
- §D.5 says "Verification succeeds only when every referenced entry exists exactly
  once and every checksum matches" — a checksum test, not a rule that the verifier
  RECOMPUTES the canonical definition identity from liasse.json and compares it to
  the claimed `definition.identity`.

If liasse.json is only covered by `definition.identity` and the verifier does not
recompute it, a semantic swap of the definition passes verification (a real
authenticity hole). If liasse.json is a byte-checksummed entry, or the verifier
recomputes §D.4, the swap is rejected. The spec does not decide between these, so
the outcome of restoring the swapped artifact is unspecified.'''

  package: {
    $liasse: 1
    $app: "t.defswap@1.0.0"
    $model: {
      notes: {
        $key: "id"
        id: "text"
        body: { $type: "text", $check: ["size(.) <= 100", "too long"] }
      }
      $mut: {
        put: [
          "n = .notes + { id: @id, body: @body }"
          "return n { id, body }"
        ]
      }
      all: { $view: ".notes { id, body, $sort: [id] }" }
      $public: {
        notes: {
          $view: ".all"
          $mut: { put: ".put" }
        }
      }
    }
  }

  steps: [
    { call: "public.notes.put", args: { id: "n1", body: "hi" },
      expect: { outcome: ok, value: { id: "n1", body: "hi" } } }
    { export: { as: "a1" }, expect: { outcome: ok } }
    // swap liasse.json for a different valid definition (loosen the body $check
    // bound) WITHOUT updating manifest.definition.identity; do not touch the
    // definition identity claim.
    { tamper_artifact: { from: "a1", as: "a1x", ops: [
      { edit_json: { path: "liasse.json",
                     pointer: "/$model/notes/body/$check/0", value: "size(.) <= 100000" } }
    ] } }
    { in_sandbox: "s1", steps: [
      { restore: { from: "a1x" },
        expect: { outcome: unspecified, violates: ["§D.4", "§D.5", "§19.5"],
                  detail: "liasse.json byte integrity vs canonical definition identity is not decided by the spec" } }
    ] }
  ]
}
